cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This paper primarily focuses on the privacy and security aspects of Zcash, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper also discusses the societal implications of privacy in cryptocurrencies, which could fall under the category of computers and society. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The use of mix networks to enhance the privacy guarantees of Zcash involves distributed computing, which could fall under this category. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses the privacy concessions made by Zcash and proposes an extension to tackle security challenges, which could involve database management. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed extension of Zcash involves addressing security challenges at the network layer, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
